DSA-001C

### **Definition:**

A number is **prime** if it is greater than 1 and divisible only by 1 and itself.

### **Logic (Simple Words):**

- If the number is **less than or equal to 1 â†’ Not Prime**
- Else check from 2 to âˆšn:
    - If any number divides `n` â†’ **Not Prime**
    - Else â†’ **Prime**

**Flow Steps: (Pseudocode)**

```
Start

â†“

Input n

â†“

Is n <= 1?

â†’ Yes â†’ Print "Not Prime" â†’ End

â†’ No

â†“

Set i = 2

Repeat while i*i <= n

â†’ If n % i == 0 â†’ Print "Not Prime" â†’ End

â†’ Else i = i + 1

â†“

Print "Prime"

â†“

End
```

ðŸ’» Java Code

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class PrimeCheck {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        boolean isPrime = true;

        if (n <= 1) {
            isPrime = false;
        } else {
            for (int i = 2; i * i <= n; i++) {
                if (n % i == 0) {
                    isPrime = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        if (isPrime)
            System.out.println("Prime");
        else
            System.out.println("Not Prime");
    }
}

```
